ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Age in years
Visit name
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2, Daily

ElementDescription: Version/code of assessment
Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: staff ID
20-meter walk: trial 1 number of steps
20-meter walk: trial 1 result
Notes: 1= Completed; 2= Not attempted, unable; 3= Attempted, unable to complete

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: trial 1 time to complete (sec.hundredths/sec)
20-meter walk: trial 2 number of steps
20-meter walk: trial 2 result
Notes: 1= Completed; 2= Not attempted, unable; 3= Attempted, unable to complete

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: trial 2 time to complete (sec.hundredths/sec)
20-meter walk: using walking aid such as cane
20-meter walk: left knee pain, current severity
Notes: 0=No pain; 10=Pain as bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: left knee pain, maximum amount experienced during walk
Notes: 0=No pain; 10=Pain as bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: right knee pain, current severity
Notes: 0=No pain; 10=Pain as bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: right knee pain, maximum amount experienced during walk
Notes: 0=No pain; 10=Pain as bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: 20-meter walk: pace (m/sec)

400-meter walk eligibility: able to complete trial 1 and trial 2 of the 20-meter walk

400-meter walk eligibility: had to see or call doctor for worsening angina (chest or heart pain) or worsening shortness of breath, past 3 months
400-meter walk eligibility: meets new or old diastolic blood pressure exclusion criterion
Notes: 0=Does not meet criterion; 1=Meets exclusion criterion; Blank = Missing Form/Incomplete Workbook

ElementDescription: 400-meter walk eligibility: meets new or old hospitalization/surgery exclusion criteria

ElementDescription: 400-meter walk eligibility: meets new or old systolic blood pressure exclusion criterion

ElementDescription: 400-meter walk eligibility: meets old or new heart rate exclusion criterion

ElementDescription: 400-meter walk eligibility: use walker or quad cane when walk

ElementDescription: 400-meter walk: completion status
Notes: 1= Completed test without stopping; 2= Completed test with one or more rests; 3= Attempted, unable to complete; 4= Not attempted, excluded; 5= Not attempted, other
